{title: Mockingbird Hill}
{artist: Slim Whitman}
{composer: unknown}

[C]When the [G7]sun in the morning peeps [C]over the hill
And [D7]kisses the roses 'round [G7]my windowsill
Then my heart fills with gladness when [C]I hear the trill
Of the [D7]birds in the treetops on [G7]Mockingbird Hill
Tra-la-la twiddly-dee-dee-dee it [C]gives me a [G7]thrill
To [D7]wake up in the morning to the [G7]mockingbird's trill
Tra-la-la twiddly-dee-dee there's [C]peace and good[G7]will
You're [D7]welcome as the flowers on [G7]Mockingbird Hill
Got a three cornered plow and an [C]acre to till
And a [D7]mule that I bought for a [G7]ten dollar bill
There's a tumble down shack and a [C]old rusty mill
But it's [D7]my home sweet home on [G7]Mockingbird Hill
When it's late in the evening I [C]climb up the hill
And sur[D7]vey all my kingdom while [G7]every thing's still
Only me and the sky and an [C]old whippoorwill
It's [D7]my home sweet home on [G7]Mockingbird Hill
